cs.HC, cs.SI, q-bio.QM, q-bio.TO, cs.GR

The paper presents a strategy for generating visualizations of biological networks using a hybrid approach that combines crowdworkers and a simulated annealing algorithm. The focus is on creating layouts that convey domain knowledge and meaning, which suggests a human-computer interaction (HCI) perspective. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also deals with graph layout algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with biological networks, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods) and q-bio.TO (Other Topics in Quantitative Biology). Finally, the paper presents a game with a purpose (GWAP), which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
